      ],
      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09B\",\"process_rule\":\"Process J09B:\\n\\n1. Make a copy of decision_table with TOURS starting with 'J09B' named 'J09B_temp'.\\n2. Update 'J09B_temp' by adding an additional empty column 'ENTSCHEIDUNG'.\\n3. Apply the following rule to J09B_temp (grouped/aggregated as needed):\\n   a. Count the number of EQUNR for every HAUS.\\n   b. If there are fewer than 3 EQUNR for a given HAUS, set ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'KSA' for those rows.\\n   c. Otherwise (3 or more EQUNR), set ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'EVU' for those rows.\\n4. JOIN J09B_temp with the EABLG table using INSTALLATION (ANLAGE) as the join key.\\n5. JOIN the result with the NET_MASTER table and the SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR as the join key.\\n6. For each joined record, compare sales data and net data for the corresponding IDs:\\n   a. If sales data is present, take the sales data fields and clear/empty the corresponding net data fields.\\n   b. If no sales data is present, retain the net data fields and clear/empty the corresponding sales data fields.\\n7. Export the final dataset as a CSV file named 'J09B.csv' including exactly these columns:\\n   - Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.\\n   - HAUS\\n   - ANLAGE\\n   - ME_MA_ID\\n   - EQUNR\\n   - HOUSE_NUM1\\n   - ENTSCHEIDUNG\\n   - TITLE\\n   - FORENAME\\n   - SURNAME\\n   - STREET\\n   - STREETNO\\n   - POST_CODE1\\n   - CITY1\\n   - CITY2\\n   - EMAIL\\n8. Send the CSV file J09B.csv via email to the EVU team at 'meter.readings@evu.com'.\\n9. After successfully exporting and sending the data, delete the temporary table 'J09B_temp'.\"}",
            "id": "lc_f3d7b442-9d24-4eaa-8cdc-993e4eec3f25"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "b113dd9e-e0ea-465b-ab1a-0162e3135fea",
        "tool_call_id": "call_oncNUH5JfK5uinOS9zpzv3Q0",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09B",
            "process_rule": "Process J09B:\n\n1. Make a copy of decision_table with TOURS starting with 'J09B' named 'J09B_temp'.\n2. Update 'J09B_temp' by adding an additional empty column 'ENTSCHEIDUNG'.\n3. Apply the following rule to J09B_temp (grouped/aggregated as needed):\n   a. Count the number of EQUNR for every HAUS.\n   b. If there are fewer than 3 EQUNR for a given HAUS, set ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'KSA' for those rows.\n   c. Otherwise (3 or more EQUNR), set ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'EVU' for those rows.\n4. JOIN J09B_temp with the EABLG table using INSTALLATION (ANLAGE) as the join key.\n5. JOIN the result with the NET_MASTER table and the SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR as the join key.\n6. For each joined record, compare sales data and net data for the corresponding IDs:\n   a. If sales data is present, take the sales data fields and clear/empty the corresponding net data fields.\n   b. If no sales data is present, retain the net data fields and clear/empty the corresponding sales data fields.\n7. Export the final dataset as a CSV file named 'J09B.csv' including exactly these columns:\n   - Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.\n   - HAUS\n   - ANLAGE\n   - ME_MA_ID\n   - EQUNR\n   - HOUSE_NUM1\n   - ENTSCHEIDUNG\n   - TITLE\n   - FORENAME\n   - SURNAME\n   - STREET\n   - STREETNO\n   - POST_CODE1\n   - CITY1\n   - CITY2\n   - EMAIL\n8. Send the CSV file J09B.csv via email to the EVU team at 'meter.readings@evu.com'.\n9. After successfully exporting and sending the data, delete the temporary table 'J09B_temp'."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
